1. Set Up Your Environment
Make sure Python is installed. You can download it from: https://www.python.org/downloads

✅ 2. Install Required Packages
Open Command Prompt (Windows) or Terminal (Mac/Linux) and run:

bash
CopyEdit
pip install opencv-python numpy
✅ 3. Save the Code
Open a code editor like VS Code, Notepad++, or simply use Notepad.

Paste the code into a new file.

Save it as:

CopyEdit
obstacle_avoidance.py
✅ 4. Run the Code
In your terminal or command prompt, navigate to the folder where you saved the file. For example:

bash
CopyEdit
cd C:\Users\YourName\Documents
Then run:

bash
CopyEdit
python obstacle_avoidance.py
✅ 5. Allow Camera Access
The program will use your webcam to simulate obstacle detection. Make sure:

Your camera is connected and not being used by another app.

You allow Python access to your webcam (you may get a popup if you're on Windows).

✅ 6. Control & Quit
The program will open a window showing the live video feed.

It will display boxes around obstacles and print the AI navigation action (like "Turn Right" or "Move Forward").

Press q to quit the application and close the window.

